    "description": "Adding more support for non-square plot windows.  This introduces an aspect calculation.  In addition, send the bbox_inches='tight' keyword in to the canvase.print_figure command to tighten up the whitespace surrounding all of the axes/labels.\r\n\r\nPossible issues people might have are:\r\n1) Using bbox_inches='tight' will make image sizes inconsistent (i.e. might be 985 \u00d7 885 pixels or something like that.  However, this minimizes whitespace.\r\n\r\n2) Images are strictly smaller than 1000x1000.  For example a 2x1 window will have something like 1000x500 pixels instead of 2000x1000.  This was done to protect against very large images that could result from, say, an aspect ratio of 50:1 producing a 50,000x1000 image.\r\n\r\n3) Using bbox_inches='tight' may make image saving slower, but it sure does make it look better!\r\n\r\nThis has been tested on x,y,z SlicePlot and ProjectionPlot with varying aspect ratios.\r\n\r\nUpdate 1: reverted a [1] -> [0], which i'm not sure where it came from.",
    "created_on": "2012-07-31T20:59:32.100966+00:00",
